      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BOHDAN (6) showed good pace from out wide and was prominent early but began to paddle and faded out of it when 5th at The Meadows in Mix 6/7 company. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Better than last start and worth following up. NARINGAL LAD (3) has been out of the placings at his last couple but on the winners' heels when placing three back (30.72) in a Grade 6 at The Meadows. Well placed here and can atone this time. CRACKERJACK GREG (1) continued his winning form with another strong run after running them ragged to make it two in a row, scoring at Shepparton over 450m (25.76). Ran the fastest time on the program in his latest win. Should be in this for a long way. PAW VOLTRON (5) is in the mix despite finishing out of the placings here last start.",
